title: Median age of the population in New Zealand 2015
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Median age in years. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Median age in years has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 1995 and 2000.
The highest Median age in years, of value 43.7 was reached at Year 2050
Minimum Median age in years about 25.6 was reached at Year 1970
min_summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Median age in years, containing a total of 21 data points.
Overall Median age in years has increased over the Year.

Median age in years is slightly decreasing from 1950 to 1965, roughly constant from 1965 to 1970, rapidly increasing from 1970 to 2005, roughly constant from 2005 to 2020, slightly increasing from 2020 to 2035, and finally roughly constant from 2035 to 2050.
